article.description: Kimbal Mackenzie had 27 points as Bucknell got past Holy Cross 77-65 in the Patriot League Conference Tourney quarterfinals on Thursday night.
article.headline: Mackenzie scores 27 to lead Bucknell past Holy Cross 77-65
article.linkText: Mackenzie scores 27 to lead Bucknell past Holy Cross 77-65
article.story: LEWISBURG, Pa. -- Kimbal Mackenzie had 27 points as Bucknell got past Holy Cross 77-65 in the Patriot League Conference Tourney quarterfinals on Thursday night. John Meeks had 14 points for Bucknell (20-11). Nate Sestina added 14 points and nine rebounds. Austin Butler had 13 points for the Crusaders (16-17). Jehyve Floyd added 13 points. Jacob Grandison had 13 points and nine rebounds. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
